definition: to jab/to poke/to stab/to sprain/to blunt/to fuck (vulgar)/to stand sth upright

sentences.chinese: 这件邮包盖着伦敦的邮戳。

sentences.english: You leave your stamp in the found logbook and use the stamp in the found box to stamp your own logbook.
sentences.chinese: 你在日志前盖在邮戳，然后把邮票贴在盒子上。

sentences.english: Copyright Office to sue and that registration provides more legal protections than a postmark ever could.
sentences.chinese: 注册比邮戳能提供更多的法律保护。

sentences.english: From the postmark he inferred where she lived .
sentences.chinese: 他从邮戳推断他住在什么哪里？

sentences.english: I see from the postmark that this card was posted from her holiday address.
sentences.chinese: 我从邮戳上看出这张明信片是从她度假的地方寄来的。

sentences.english: The cancelled postage stamps cannot be used again.
sentences.chinese: 盖过邮戳的邮票不能再用。

sentences.english: I can easily look up tracking information or read a postmark, you know.
sentences.chinese: 这通过查看邮寄信息或邮戳就可心知肚明。

sentences.english: All the letters bore an Aberdeen postmark.
sentences.chinese: 所有的信件上都盖有阿伯丁郡的邮戳。

sentences.english: A postage meter can stamp mail automatically.
sentences.chinese: 盖戳机可以自动为信件盖上邮戳。

sentences.english: A certified letter, with a faraway postmark.
sentences.chinese: 是一封挂号信，上面盖着的是一个遥远的地方的邮戳。
她在所收到的每一封信上都用邮戳盖上日期。

sentences.english: Visitors swarned to mail the special postcards with certain stampers.
sentences.chinese: 游客争先恐后地给家里邮寄盖有特别邮戳的明信片。

sentences.english: He took a used envelope bearing an Irish postmark.
sentences.chinese: 他拿了一个盖着爱尔兰邮戳的旧信封。

sentences.english: An envelope within the letter was postmarked by the Poole post office, Kisling said.
sentences.chinese: 在该信的信封上盖有普尔市邮局的邮戳，吉斯林说。

sentences.english: The letter is postmarked New York.
sentences.chinese: 这封信盖有伦敦的邮戳。

sentences.english: She received a letter postmarked Hong Kong.
sentences.chinese: 她收到一封盖有香港邮戳的信。

definition: letter sheet (similar to an aerogram but not necessarily sent by airmail)
